e belligerent, jingoistic patriot), and the Orc (the ultraviolent savage derived from a deliberate misreading of Tolkien's epic). Through these contested identities, Soviet Self-Hatred shows how stories people tell about themselves can, tragically, become the stories that others are forced to live.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aNational characteristics, Russian. 0aPost-communismzRussia (Federation). 0aRussiansxAttitudes. 4aCULTURAL STUDIES. 4aHISTORY. 7aHISTORY / Russia / Post-Soviet.2bisacsh  aRussian literature, Russian inferiority complex, Russian jokes, Orcs and Russia, popular culture in Russia, Lord of the Rings and Russia, Borat and Russia, Russian memes.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311075183308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishz978311131913108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023z9783111318189oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501769900?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501769900423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501769900/original  a978-3-11-075183-3  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131913-1  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEGb2023  aZDB-23-DGGb2023